headline: 'We've Seen A Very Strong Demand In The Art Market,' Art Auction Sales Projected To Jump 50% This Year
summary: Early reports from this week's New York fall art auctions show that experts’ sales totals predictions will be far surpassed. Sales were expected to hit $1.4 billion, CNBC reported last week, citing art experts. headline: Nvidia falls on Google–Meta news, Coinbase & Estée Lauder downgraded
summary: There are a number of stocks on the move on Tuesday, Nov. 25. Market Domination anchor Josh Lipton takes a look at a few of them. Nvidia (NVDA) stock is sliding following an Information report that Meta (META) is in talks to use Google's (GOOG, GOOGL) artificial intelligence (AI) chips. Coinbase (COIN) was downgraded to Hold from Buy at Argus. Rothschild & Co. Redburn downgraded Estée Lauder (EL) to Sell from Neutral. To watch more expert insights and analysis on the latest market action, check out more Market Domination.
